>>Gettin started

1.
install free-ware cooding program
www.sublimetext.com/3

2.
set plug-in
when your installation of sublime is complete, get in and "ctrl+shift+p" to install "packasge control"

then whenever you want to add plug-in
just remember
"ctrl+shift+p" -> "install" -> (wait till input window'll show up) type anyting you want
* recommended plug-ins:
  emmet - to make your coding faster
  bracket highlighter
  sidebar enhancement
  color picker - to use this, "ctrl+c"

3.
setting after step 2

(preference>package settings>side bar>settings user)
{  "default_browser": "chrome"  }


(preference>package settings>side bar>key binding- user)
[  { "keys": ["ctrl+b"], "command": "toggle_side_bar" },  { "keys": ["f12"], "command": "side_bar_open_in_browser" },  { "keys": ["ctrl+alt+n"], "command": "side_bar_new_file" },  { "keys": ["f2"], "command": "side_bar_rename" },  { "keys": ["ctrl+alt+m"], "command": "side_bar_move" },  { "keys": ["ctrl+alt+d"], "command": "side_bar_delete" } ] 8 


(to set korean)
(preference>package settings>emmet>settings-user)
{  "snippets": {   "variables": {   "lang": "ko",   "locale": "ko-KR",   "charset": "UTF-8",   "indentation": "\t",   "newline": "\n"  },   "html": {    "abbreviations" : { 
 
   }   }  } } 
   
   
*save each window with "ctrl+S" and when it's over "ctrl+w" to exit the window
   
   
4.
look for the right sid of botton of the sublime window, plaing text -> change it into HTML
just "enter ! and tab" then html tag is ready.


5.
준비는 다 끝났다! ㅋㅋ 반응형 웹코딩을 하자. 걍 저장하고 f12를 누르면 활용해서 브라우저에서 내 코드를 확인할수있다.
    
